  "text": "Found 7 reference files in sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0 showing typed client patterns for implementing a CRD client. (1) rest/client.go defines rest.Interface (Get/Post/Put/Patch/Delete/Verb methods) and RESTClient struct, the foundation all typed clients use. (2) kubernetes/typed/core/v1/pod.go shows the resource client pattern: PodInterface defines Create/Get/List/Update/Delete/Watch/Patch signatures (all taking context.Context), pods struct embeds gentype.ClientWithListAndApply[*Pod, *PodList, *PodApplyConfiguration], newPods constructor passes resource name, rest client, namespace, and object factories. (3) gentype/type.go contains the generic CRUD implementations: Create uses client.Post().Resource().Body().Do().Into(), Get uses client.Get().Resource().Name().Do().Into(), List uses client.Get().Resource().Timeout().Do().Into(), Delete uses client.Delete().Resource().Name().Body().Do().Error(). (4) core_client.go shows the group-version client pattern: CoreV1Interface embeds per-resource Getter interfaces, CoreV1Client holds restClient rest.Interface, setConfigDefaults sets APIPath=/api. (5) apps_client.go shows non-core groups use APIPath=/apis. (6) kubernetes/scheme/register.go shows Scheme, Codecs, and ParameterCodec setup. For CRDs, agent should use APIPath=/apis and register custom types in a scheme.",
